39/* Opcode modifiers. */
40#define MOD_Gap 0 /* Eats a parameter / does nothing */
41#define MOD_PreAdd 1 /* Parameter adds to "special" prefix */
42#define MOD_Op0Add 2 /* Parameter adds to opcode byte 0 */
43#define MOD_Op1Add 3 /* Parameter adds to opcode byte 1 */
44#define MOD_Op2Add 4 /* Parameter adds to opcode byte 2 */
45#define MOD_SpAdd 5 /* Parameter adds to "spare" value */
46#define MOD_OpSizeR 6 /* Parameter replaces opersize */
47#define MOD_Imm8 7 /* Parameter is included as immediate byte */
48#define MOD_AdSizeR 8 /* Parameter replaces addrsize (jmp only) */
49#define MOD_DOpS64R 9 /* Parameter replaces default 64-bit opersize */
50#define MOD_Op1AddSp 10 /* Parameter is added as "spare" to opcode byte 2 */
51#define MOD_SetVEX 11 /* Parameter replaces internal VEX prefix value */
52
53/* GAS suffix flags for instructions */
54enum x86_gas_suffix_flags {
55 SUF_Z = 1<<0, /* no suffix */
56 SUF_B = 1<<1,
57 SUF_W = 1<<2,
58 SUF_L = 1<<3,
59 SUF_Q = 1<<4,
60 SUF_S = 1<<5,
61 SUF_MASK = SUF_Z|SUF_B|SUF_W|SUF_L|SUF_Q|SUF_S,
62
63 /* Flags only used in x86_insn_info */
64 GAS_ONLY = 1<<6, /* Only available in GAS mode */
65 GAS_ILLEGAL = 1<<7, /* Illegal in GAS mode */
66 GAS_NO_REV = 1<<8 /* Don't reverse operands in GAS mode */
67};
68
69/* Miscellaneous flag tests for instructions */
70enum x86_misc_flags {
71 /* These are tested against BITS==64. */
72 ONLY_64 = 1<<0, /* Only available in 64-bit mode */
73 NOT_64 = 1<<1, /* Not available (invalid) in 64-bit mode */
74 /* These are tested against whether the base instruction is an AVX one. */
75 ONLY_AVX = 1<<2, /* Only available in AVX instruction */
76 NOT_AVX = 1<<3 /* Not available (invalid) in AVX instruction */
77};

79enum x86_operand_type {
80 OPT_Imm = 0, /* immediate */
81 OPT_Reg = 1, /* any general purpose or FPU register */
82 OPT_Mem = 2, /* memory */
83 OPT_RM = 3, /* any general purpose or FPU register OR memory */
84 OPT_SIMDReg = 4, /* any MMX or XMM register */
85 OPT_SIMDRM = 5, /* any MMX or XMM register OR memory */
86 OPT_SegReg = 6, /* any segment register */
87 OPT_CRReg = 7, /* any CR register */
88 OPT_DRReg = 8, /* any DR register */
89 OPT_TRReg = 9, /* any TR register */
90 OPT_ST0 = 10, /* ST0 */
91 OPT_Areg = 11, /* AL/AX/EAX/RAX (depending on size) */
92 OPT_Creg = 12, /* CL/CX/ECX/RCX (depending on size) */
93 OPT_Dreg = 13, /* DL/DX/EDX/RDX (depending on size) */
94 OPT_CS = 14, /* CS */
95 OPT_DS = 15, /* DS */
96 OPT_ES = 16, /* ES */
97 OPT_FS = 17, /* FS */
98 OPT_GS = 18, /* GS */
99 OPT_SS = 19, /* SS */
100 OPT_CR4 = 20, /* CR4 */
101 /* memory offset (an EA, but with no registers allowed)
102 * [special case for MOV opcode]
103 */
104 OPT_MemOffs = 21,
105 OPT_Imm1 = 22, /* immediate, value=1 (for special-case shift) */
106 /* immediate, does not contain SEG:OFF (for jmp/call) */
107 OPT_ImmNotSegOff = 23,
108 OPT_XMM0 = 24, /* XMM0 */
109 /* AX/EAX/RAX memory operand only (EA) [special case for SVM opcodes]
110 */
111 OPT_MemrAX = 25,
112 /* EAX memory operand only (EA) [special case for SVM skinit opcode] */
113 OPT_MemEAX = 26,
114 /* XMM VSIB memory operand */
115 OPT_MemXMMIndex = 27,
116 /* YMM VSIB memory operand */
117 OPT_MemYMMIndex = 28
118};

120enum x86_operand_size {
121 /* any size acceptable/no size spec acceptable (dep. on strict) */
122 OPS_Any = 0,
123 /* 8/16/32/64/80/128/256 bits (from user or reg size) */
124 OPS_8 = 1,
125 OPS_16 = 2,
126 OPS_32 = 3,
127 OPS_64 = 4,
128 OPS_80 = 5,
129 OPS_128 = 6,
130 OPS_256 = 7,
131 /* current BITS setting; when this is used the size matched
132 * gets stored into the opersize as well.
133 */
134 OPS_BITS = 8
135};
136
137enum x86_operand_targetmod {
138 OPTM_None = 0, /* no target mod acceptable */
139 OPTM_Near = 1, /* NEAR */
140 OPTM_Short = 2, /* SHORT */
141 OPTM_Far = 3, /* FAR (or SEG:OFF immediate) */
142 OPTM_To = 4 /* TO */
143};
144
145enum x86_operand_action {
146 OPA_None = 0, /* does nothing (operand data is discarded) */
147 OPA_EA = 1, /* operand data goes into ea field */
148 OPA_Imm = 2, /* operand data goes into imm field */
149 OPA_SImm = 3, /* operand data goes into sign-extended imm field */
150 OPA_Spare = 4, /* operand data goes into "spare" field */
151 OPA_Op0Add = 5, /* operand data is added to opcode byte 0 */
152 OPA_Op1Add = 6, /* operand data is added to opcode byte 1 */
153 /* operand data goes into BOTH ea and spare
154 * (special case for imul opcode)
155 */
156 OPA_SpareEA = 7,
157 /* relative jump (outputs a jmp instead of normal insn) */
158 OPA_JmpRel = 8,
159 /* operand size goes into address size (jmp only) */
160 OPA_AdSizeR = 9,
161 /* far jump (outputs a farjmp instead of normal insn) */
162 OPA_JmpFar = 10,
163 /* ea operand only sets address size (no actual ea field) */
164 OPA_AdSizeEA = 11,
165 OPA_VEX = 12, /* operand data goes into VEX/XOP "vvvv" field */
166 /* operand data goes into BOTH VEX/XOP "vvvv" field and ea field */
167 OPA_EAVEX = 13,
168 /* operand data goes into BOTH VEX/XOP "vvvv" field and spare field */
169 OPA_SpareVEX = 14,
170 /* operand data goes into upper 4 bits of immediate byte (VEX is4 field) */
171 OPA_VEXImmSrc = 15,
172 /* operand data goes into bottom 4 bits of immediate byte
173 * (currently only VEX imz2 field)
174 */
175 OPA_VEXImm = 16
176};
177
178enum x86_operand_post_action {
179 OPAP_None = 0,
180 /* sign-extended imm8 that could expand to a large imm16/32 */
181 OPAP_SImm8 = 1,
182 /* could become a short opcode mov with bits=64 and a32 prefix */
183 OPAP_ShortMov = 2,
184 /* forced 16-bit address size (override ignored, no prefix) */
185 OPAP_A16 = 3,
186 /* large imm64 that can become a sign-extended imm32 */
187 OPAP_SImm32Avail = 4
188};

190typedef struct x86_info_operand {
191 /* Operand types. These are more detailed than the "general" types for all
192 * architectures, as they include the size, for instance.
193 */
194
195 /* general type (must be exact match, except for RM types): */
196 unsigned int type:5;
197
198 /* size (user-specified, or from register size) */
199 unsigned int size:4;
200
201 /* size implicit or explicit ("strictness" of size matching on
202 * non-registers -- registers are always strictly matched):
203 * 0 = user size must exactly match size above.
204 * 1 = user size either unspecified or exactly match size above.
205 */
206 unsigned int relaxed:1;
207
208 /* effective address size
209 * 0 = any address size allowed except for 64-bit
210 * 1 = only 64-bit address size allowed
211 */
212 unsigned int eas64:1;
213
214 /* target modification */
215 unsigned int targetmod:3;
216
217 /* Actions: what to do with the operand if the instruction matches.
218 * Essentially describes what part of the output bytecode gets the
219 * operand. This may require conversion (e.g. a register going into
220 * an ea field). Naturally, only one of each of these may be contained
221 * in the operands of a single insn_info structure.
222 */
223 unsigned int action:5;
224
225 /* Postponed actions: actions which can't be completed at
226 * parse-time due to possibly dependent expressions. For these, some
227 * additional data (stored in the second byte of the opcode with a
228 * one-byte opcode) is passed to later stages of the assembler with
229 * flags set to indicate postponed actions.
230 */
231 unsigned int post_action:3;
232} x86_info_operand;
233
234typedef struct x86_insn_info {
235 /* GAS suffix flags */
236 unsigned int gas_flags:9; /* Enabled for these GAS suffixes */
237
238 /* Tests against BITS==64, AVX, and XOP */
239 unsigned int misc_flags:5;
240
241 /* The CPU feature flags needed to execute this instruction. This is OR'ed
242 * with arch-specific data[2]. This combined value is compared with
243 * cpu_enabled to see if all bits set here are set in cpu_enabled--if so,
244 * the instruction is available on this CPU.
245 */
246 unsigned int cpu0:6;
247 unsigned int cpu1:6;
248 unsigned int cpu2:6;
249
250 /* Opcode modifiers for variations of instruction. As each modifier reads
251 * its parameter in LSB->MSB order from the arch-specific data[1] from the
252 * lexer data, and the LSB of the arch-specific data[1] is reserved for the
253 * count of insn_info structures in the instruction grouping, there can
254 * only be a maximum of 3 modifiers.
255 */
256 unsigned char modifiers[3];
257
258 /* Operand Size */
259 unsigned char opersize;
260
261 /* Default operand size in 64-bit mode (0 = 32-bit for readability). */
262 unsigned char def_opersize_64;
263
264 /* A special instruction prefix, used for some of the Intel SSE and SSE2
265 * instructions. Intel calls these 3-byte opcodes, but in AMD64's 64-bit
266 * mode, they're treated like normal prefixes (e.g. the REX prefix needs
267 * to be *after* the F2/F3/66 "prefix").
268 * (0=no special prefix)
269 * 0xC0 - 0xCF indicate a VEX prefix, with the four LSBs holding "WLpp":
270 * W: VEX.W field (meaning depends on opcode)
271 * L: 0=128-bit, 1=256-bit
272 * pp: SIMD prefix designation:
273 * 00: None
274 * 01: 66
275 * 10: F3
276 * 11: F2
277 * 0x80 - 0x8F indicate a XOP prefix, with the four LSBs holding "WLpp":
278 * same meanings as VEX prefix.
279 */
280 unsigned char special_prefix;
281
282 /* The length of the basic opcode */
283 unsigned char opcode_len;
284
285 /* The basic 1-3 byte opcode (not including the special instruction
286 * prefix).
287 */
288 unsigned char opcode[3];
289
290 /* The 3-bit "spare" value (extended opcode) for the R/M byte field */
291 unsigned char spare;
292
293 /* The number of operands this form of the instruction takes */
294 unsigned int num_operands:4;
295
296 /* The index into the insn_operands array which contains the type of each
297 * operand, see above
298 */
299 unsigned int operands_index:12;
300} x86_insn_info;
301
302typedef struct x86_id_insn {
303 yasm_insn insn; /* base structure */
304
305 /* instruction parse group - NULL if empty instruction (just prefixes) */
306 /*@null@*/ const x86_insn_info *group;
307
308 /* CPU feature flags enabled at the time of parsing the instruction */
309 wordptr cpu_enabled;
310
311 /* Modifier data */
312 unsigned char mod_data[3];
313
314 /* Number of elements in the instruction parse group */
315 unsigned int num_info:8;
316
317 /* BITS setting active at the time of parsing the instruction */
318 unsigned int mode_bits:8;
319
320 /* Suffix flags */
321 unsigned int suffix:9;
322
323 /* Tests against BITS==64 and AVX */
324 unsigned int misc_flags:5;
325
326 /* Parser enabled at the time of parsing the instruction */
327 unsigned int parser:2;
328
329 /* Strict forced setting at the time of parsing the instruction */
330 unsigned int force_strict:1;
331
332 /* Default rel setting at the time of parsing the instruction */
333 unsigned int default_rel:1;
334} x86_id_insn;

353/* Looks for the first SIMD register match for the purposes of VSIB matching.
354 * Full legality checking is performed in EA code.
355 */
356static int
357x86_expr_contains_simd_cb(const yasm_expr__item *ei, void *d)
358{
359 int ymm = *((int *)d);
360 if (ei->type != YASM_EXPR_REG)
361 return 0;
362 switch ((x86_expritem_reg_size)(ei->data.reg & ~0xFUL)) {
363 case X86_XMMREG:
364 if (!ymm)
365 return 1;
366 break;
367 case X86_YMMREG:
368 if (ymm)
369 return 1;
370 break;
371 default:
372 break;
373 }
374 return 0;
375}
376
377static int
378x86_expr_contains_simd(const yasm_expr *e, int ymm)
379{
380 return yasm_expr__traverse_leaves_in_const(e, &ymm,
381 x86_expr_contains_simd_cb);
382}

384static void
385x86_finalize_common(x86_common *common, const x86_insn_info *info,
386 unsigned int mode_bits)
387{
388 common->addrsize = 0;
389 common->opersize = info->opersize;
390 common->lockrep_pre = 0;
391 common->acqrel_pre = 0;
392 common->mode_bits = (unsigned char)mode_bits;
393}

395static void
396x86_finalize_opcode(x86_opcode *opcode, const x86_insn_info *info)
397{
398 opcode->len = info->opcode_len;
399 opcode->opcode[0] = info->opcode[0];
400 opcode->opcode[1] = info->opcode[1];
401 opcode->opcode[2] = info->opcode[2];
402}

404/* Clear operands so they don't get destroyed after we've copied references. */
405static void
406x86_id_insn_clear_operands(x86_id_insn *id_insn)
407{
408 yasm_insn_operand *op = yasm_insn_ops_first(&id_insn->insn);
409 while (op) {
410 op->type = YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG;
411 op = yasm_insn_op_next(op);
412 }
413}

415static void
416x86_finalize_jmpfar(yasm_bytecode *bc, yasm_bytecode *prev_bc,
417 const x86_insn_info *info)
418{
419 x86_id_insn *id_insn = (x86_id_insn *)bc->contents;
420 unsigned char *mod_data = id_insn->mod_data;
421 unsigned int mode_bits = id_insn->mode_bits;
422 x86_jmpfar *jmpfar;
423 yasm_insn_operand *op;
424 unsigned int i;
425
426 jmpfar = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(x86_jmpfar));
427 x86_finalize_common(&jmpfar->common, info, mode_bits);
428 x86_finalize_opcode(&jmpfar->opcode, info);
429
430 op = yasm_insn_ops_first(&id_insn->insn);
431
432 if (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_IMM && op->seg) {
433 /* SEG:OFF */
434 if (yasm_value_finalize_expr(&jmpfar->segment, op->seg, prev_bc, 16))
435 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TOO_COMPLEX,
436 N_("jump target segment too complex"));
437 if (yasm_value_finalize_expr(&jmpfar->offset, op->data.val, prev_bc,
438 0))
439 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TOO_COMPLEX,
440 N_("jump target offset too complex"));
441 } else if (op->targetmod == X86_FAR) {
442 /* "FAR imm" target needs to become "seg imm:imm". */
443 yasm_expr *e = yasm_expr_create_branch(YASM_EXPR_SEG,
444 yasm_expr_copy(op->data.val),
445 op->data.val->line);
446 if (yasm_value_finalize_expr(&jmpfar->offset, op->data.val, prev_bc, 0)
447 || yasm_value_finalize_expr(&jmpfar->segment, e, prev_bc, 16))
448 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TOO_COMPLEX,
449 N_("jump target expression too complex"));
450 } else if (yasm_insn_op_next(op)) {
451 /* Two operand form (gas) */
452 yasm_insn_operand *op2 = yasm_insn_op_next(op);
453 if (yasm_value_finalize_expr(&jmpfar->segment, op->data.val, prev_bc,
454 16))
455 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TOO_COMPLEX,
456 N_("jump target segment too complex"));
457 if (yasm_value_finalize_expr(&jmpfar->offset, op2->data.val, prev_bc,
458 0))
459 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TOO_COMPLEX,
460 N_("jump target offset too complex"));
461 if (op2->size == OPS_BITS)
462 jmpfar->common.opersize = (unsigned char)mode_bits;
463 } else
464 yasm_internal_error(N_("didn't get FAR expression in jmpfar"));
465
466 /* Apply modifiers */
467 for (i=0; i<NELEMS(info->modifiers); i++) {
468 switch (info->modifiers[i]) {
469 case MOD_Gap:
470 break;
471 case MOD_Op0Add:
472 jmpfar->opcode.opcode[0] += mod_data[i];
473 break;
474 case MOD_Op1Add:
475 jmpfar->opcode.opcode[1] += mod_data[i];
476 break;
477 case MOD_Op2Add:
478 jmpfar->opcode.opcode[2] += mod_data[i];
479 break;
480 case MOD_Op1AddSp:
481 jmpfar->opcode.opcode[1] += mod_data[i]<<3;
482 break;
483 default:
484 break;
485 }
486 }
487
488 yasm_x86__bc_apply_prefixes((x86_common *)jmpfar, NULL,
489 info->def_opersize_64,
490 id_insn->insn.num_prefixes,
491 id_insn->insn.prefixes);
492
493 x86_id_insn_clear_operands(id_insn);
494
495 /* Transform the bytecode */
496 yasm_x86__bc_transform_jmpfar(bc, jmpfar);
497}

499static void
500x86_finalize_jmp(yasm_bytecode *bc, yasm_bytecode *prev_bc,
501 const x86_insn_info *jinfo)
502{
503 x86_id_insn *id_insn = (x86_id_insn *)bc->contents;
504 x86_jmp *jmp;
505 int num_info = id_insn->num_info;
506 const x86_insn_info *info = id_insn->group;
507 unsigned char *mod_data = id_insn->mod_data;
508 unsigned int mode_bits = id_insn->mode_bits;
509 /*unsigned char suffix = id_insn->suffix;*/
510 yasm_insn_operand *op;
511 static const unsigned char size_lookup[] =
512 {0, 8, 16, 32, 64, 80, 128, 0, 0}; /* 256 not needed */
513 unsigned int i;
514
515 /* We know the target is in operand 0, but sanity check for Imm. */
516 op = yasm_insn_ops_first(&id_insn->insn);
517 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_IMM)
518 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand conversion"));
519
520 jmp = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(x86_jmp));
521 x86_finalize_common(&jmp->common, jinfo, mode_bits);
522 if (yasm_value_finalize_expr(&jmp->target, op->data.val, prev_bc, 0))
523 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TOO_COMPLEX,
524 N_("jump target expression too complex"));
525 if (jmp->target.seg_of || jmp->target.rshift || jmp->target.curpos_rel)
526 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE, N_("invalid jump target"));
527 yasm_value_set_curpos_rel(&jmp->target, bc, 0);
528 jmp->target.jump_target = 1;
529
530 /* See if the user explicitly specified short/near/far. */
531 switch (insn_operands[jinfo->operands_index+0].targetmod) {
532 case OPTM_Short:
533 jmp->op_sel = JMP_SHORT_FORCED;
534 break;
535 case OPTM_Near:
536 jmp->op_sel = JMP_NEAR_FORCED;
537 break;
538 default:
539 jmp->op_sel = JMP_NONE;
540 }
541
542 /* Check for address size setting in second operand, if present */
543 if (jinfo->num_operands > 1 &&
544 insn_operands[jinfo->operands_index+1].action == OPA_AdSizeR)
545 jmp->common.addrsize = (unsigned char)
546 size_lookup[insn_operands[jinfo->operands_index+1].size];
547
548 /* Check for address size override */
549 for (i=0; i<NELEMS(jinfo->modifiers); i++) {
550 if (jinfo->modifiers[i] == MOD_AdSizeR)
551 jmp->common.addrsize = mod_data[i];
552 }
553
554 /* Scan through other infos for this insn looking for short/near versions.
555 * Needs to match opersize and number of operands, also be within CPU.
556 */
557 jmp->shortop.len = 0;
558 jmp->nearop.len = 0;
559 for (; num_info>0 && (jmp->shortop.len == 0 || jmp->nearop.len == 0);
560 num_info--, info++) {
561 /* Match CPU */
562 if (mode_bits != 64 && (info->misc_flags & ONLY_64))
563 continue;
564 if (mode_bits == 64 && (info->misc_flags & NOT_64))
565 continue;
566
567 if (!BitVector_bit_test(id_insn->cpu_enabled, info->cpu0) ||
568 !BitVector_bit_test(id_insn->cpu_enabled, info->cpu1) ||
569 !BitVector_bit_test(id_insn->cpu_enabled, info->cpu2))
570 continue;
571
572 if (info->num_operands == 0)
573 continue;
574
575 if (insn_operands[info->operands_index+0].action != OPA_JmpRel)
576 continue;
577
578 if (info->opersize != jmp->common.opersize)
579 continue;
580
581 switch (insn_operands[info->operands_index+0].targetmod) {
582 case OPTM_Short:
583 x86_finalize_opcode(&jmp->shortop, info);
584 for (i=0; i<NELEMS(info->modifiers); i++) {
585 if (info->modifiers[i] == MOD_Op0Add)
586 jmp->shortop.opcode[0] += mod_data[i];
587 }
588 break;
589 case OPTM_Near:
590 x86_finalize_opcode(&jmp->nearop, info);
591 for (i=0; i<NELEMS(info->modifiers); i++) {
592 if (info->modifiers[i] == MOD_Op1Add)
593 jmp->nearop.opcode[1] += mod_data[i];
594 }
595 break;
596 }
597 }
598
599 if ((jmp->op_sel == JMP_SHORT_FORCED) && (jmp->shortop.len == 0))
600 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TYPE,
601 N_("no SHORT form of that jump instruction exists"));
602 if ((jmp->op_sel == JMP_NEAR_FORCED) && (jmp->nearop.len == 0))
603 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TYPE,
604 N_("no NEAR form of that jump instruction exists"));
605
606 if (jmp->op_sel == JMP_NONE) {
607 if (jmp->nearop.len == 0)
608 jmp->op_sel = JMP_SHORT_FORCED;
609 if (jmp->shortop.len == 0)
610 jmp->op_sel = JMP_NEAR_FORCED;
611 }
612
613 yasm_x86__bc_apply_prefixes((x86_common *)jmp, NULL,
614 jinfo->def_opersize_64,
615 id_insn->insn.num_prefixes,
616 id_insn->insn.prefixes);
617
618 x86_id_insn_clear_operands(id_insn);
619
620 /* Transform the bytecode */
621 yasm_x86__bc_transform_jmp(bc, jmp);
622}
623
624static const x86_insn_info *
625x86_find_match(x86_id_insn *id_insn, yasm_insn_operand **ops,
626 yasm_insn_operand **rev_ops, const unsigned int *size_lookup,
627 int bypass)
628{
629 const x86_insn_info *info = id_insn->group;
630 unsigned int num_info = id_insn->num_info;
631 unsigned int suffix = id_insn->suffix;
632 unsigned int mode_bits = id_insn->mode_bits;
633 int found = 0;
634
635 /* Just do a simple linear search through the info array for a match.
636 * First match wins.
637 */
638 for (; num_info>0 && !found; num_info--, info++) {
639 yasm_insn_operand *op, **use_ops;
640 const x86_info_operand *info_ops =
641 &insn_operands[info->operands_index];
642 unsigned int gas_flags = info->gas_flags;
643 unsigned int misc_flags = info->misc_flags;
644 unsigned int size;
645 int mismatch = 0;
646 unsigned int i;
647
648 /* Match CPU */
649 if (mode_bits != 64 && (misc_flags & ONLY_64))
650 continue;
651 if (mode_bits == 64 && (misc_flags & NOT_64))
652 continue;
653
654 if (bypass != 8 &&
655 (!BitVector_bit_test(id_insn->cpu_enabled, info->cpu0) ||
656 !BitVector_bit_test(id_insn->cpu_enabled, info->cpu1) ||
657 !BitVector_bit_test(id_insn->cpu_enabled, info->cpu2)))
658 continue;
659
660 /* Match # of operands */
661 if (id_insn->insn.num_operands != info->num_operands)
662 continue;
663
664 /* Match AVX */
665 if (!(id_insn->misc_flags & ONLY_AVX) && (misc_flags & ONLY_AVX))
666 continue;
667 if ((id_insn->misc_flags & ONLY_AVX) && (misc_flags & NOT_AVX))
668 continue;
669
670 /* Match parser mode */
671 if ((gas_flags & GAS_ONLY) && id_insn->parser != X86_PARSER_GAS)
672 continue;
673 if ((gas_flags & GAS_ILLEGAL) && id_insn->parser == X86_PARSER_GAS)
674 continue;
675
676 /* Match suffix (if required) */
677 if (id_insn->parser == X86_PARSER_GAS
678 && ((suffix & SUF_MASK) & (gas_flags & SUF_MASK)) == 0)
679 continue;
680
681 /* Use reversed operands in GAS mode if not otherwise specified */
682 use_ops = ops;
683 if (id_insn->parser == X86_PARSER_GAS && !(gas_flags & GAS_NO_REV))
684 use_ops = rev_ops;
685
686 if (id_insn->insn.num_operands == 0) {
687 found = 1; /* no operands -> must have a match here. */
688 break;
689 }
690
691 /* Match each operand type and size */
692 for (i = 0, op = use_ops[0]; op && i<info->num_operands && !mismatch;
693 op = use_ops[++i]) {
694 /* Check operand type */
695 switch (info_ops[i].type) {
696 case OPT_Imm:
697 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_IMM)
698 mismatch = 1;
699 break;
700 case OPT_RM:
701 if (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY)
702 break;
703 /*@fallthrough@*/
704 case OPT_Reg:
705 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG)
706 mismatch = 1;
707 else {
708 switch ((x86_expritem_reg_size)(op->data.reg&~0xFUL)) {
709 case X86_REG8:
710 case X86_REG8X:
711 case X86_REG16:
712 case X86_REG32:
713 case X86_REG64:
714 case X86_FPUREG:
715 break;
716 default:
717 mismatch = 1;
718 break;
719 }
720 }
721 break;
722 case OPT_Mem:
723 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY)
724 mismatch = 1;
725 break;
726 case OPT_SIMDRM:
727 if (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY)
728 break;
729 /*@fallthrough@*/
730 case OPT_SIMDReg:
731 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG)
732 mismatch = 1;
733 else {
734 switch ((x86_expritem_reg_size)(op->data.reg&~0xFUL)) {
735 case X86_MMXREG:
736 case X86_XMMREG:
737 case X86_YMMREG:
738 break;
739 default:
740 mismatch = 1;
741 break;
742 }
743 }
744 break;
745 case OPT_SegReg:
746 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_SEGREG)
747 mismatch = 1;
748 break;
749 case OPT_CRReg:
750 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG ||
751 (op->data.reg & ~0xFUL) != X86_CRREG)
752 mismatch = 1;
753 break;
754 case OPT_DRReg:
755 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG ||
756 (op->data.reg & ~0xFUL) != X86_DRREG)
757 mismatch = 1;
758 break;
759 case OPT_TRReg:
760 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG ||
761 (op->data.reg & ~0xFUL) != X86_TRREG)
762 mismatch = 1;
763 break;
764 case OPT_ST0:
765 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG ||
766 op->data.reg != X86_FPUREG)
767 mismatch = 1;
768 break;
769 case OPT_Areg:
770 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG ||
771 (info_ops[i].size == OPS_8 &&
772 op->data.reg != (X86_REG8 | 0) &&
773 op->data.reg != (X86_REG8X | 0)) ||
774 (info_ops[i].size == OPS_16 &&
775 op->data.reg != (X86_REG16 | 0)) ||
776 (info_ops[i].size == OPS_32 &&
777 op->data.reg != (X86_REG32 | 0)) ||
778 (info_ops[i].size == OPS_64 &&
779 op->data.reg != (X86_REG64 | 0)))
780 mismatch = 1;
781 break;
782 case OPT_Creg:
783 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG ||
784 (info_ops[i].size == OPS_8 &&
785 op->data.reg != (X86_REG8 | 1) &&
786 op->data.reg != (X86_REG8X | 1)) ||
787 (info_ops[i].size == OPS_16 &&
788 op->data.reg != (X86_REG16 | 1)) ||
789 (info_ops[i].size == OPS_32 &&
790 op->data.reg != (X86_REG32 | 1)) ||
791 (info_ops[i].size == OPS_64 &&
792 op->data.reg != (X86_REG64 | 1)))
793 mismatch = 1;
794 break;
795 case OPT_Dreg:
796 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG ||
797 (info_ops[i].size == OPS_8 &&
798 op->data.reg != (X86_REG8 | 2) &&
799 op->data.reg != (X86_REG8X | 2)) ||
800 (info_ops[i].size == OPS_16 &&
801 op->data.reg != (X86_REG16 | 2)) ||
802 (info_ops[i].size == OPS_32 &&
803 op->data.reg != (X86_REG32 | 2)) ||
804 (info_ops[i].size == OPS_64 &&
805 op->data.reg != (X86_REG64 | 2)))
806 mismatch = 1;
807 break;
808 case OPT_CS:
809 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_SEGREG ||
810 (op->data.reg & 0xF) != 1)
811 mismatch = 1;
812 break;
813 case OPT_DS:
814 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_SEGREG ||
815 (op->data.reg & 0xF) != 3)
816 mismatch = 1;
817 break;
818 case OPT_ES:
819 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_SEGREG ||
820 (op->data.reg & 0xF) != 0)
821 mismatch = 1;
822 break;
823 case OPT_FS:
824 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_SEGREG ||
825 (op->data.reg & 0xF) != 4)
826 mismatch = 1;
827 break;
828 case OPT_GS:
829 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_SEGREG ||
830 (op->data.reg & 0xF) != 5)
831 mismatch = 1;
832 break;
833 case OPT_SS:
834 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_SEGREG ||
835 (op->data.reg & 0xF) != 2)
836 mismatch = 1;
837 break;
838 case OPT_CR4:
839 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG ||
840 op->data.reg != (X86_CRREG | 4))
841 mismatch = 1;
842 break;
843 case OPT_MemOffs:
844 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY ||
845 yasm_expr__contains(op->data.ea->disp.abs,
846 YASM_EXPR_REG) ||
847 op->data.ea->pc_rel ||
848 (!op->data.ea->not_pc_rel && id_insn->default_rel &&
849 op->data.ea->disp.size != 64))
850 mismatch = 1;
851 break;
852 case OPT_Imm1:
853 if (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_IMM) {
854 const yasm_intnum *num;
855 num = yasm_expr_get_intnum(&op->data.val, 0);
856 if (!num || !yasm_intnum_is_pos1(num))
857 mismatch = 1;
858 } else
859 mismatch = 1;
860 break;
861 case OPT_ImmNotSegOff:
862 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_IMM ||
863 op->targetmod != 0 || op->seg)
864 mismatch = 1;
865 break;
866 case OPT_XMM0:
867 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG ||
868 op->data.reg != X86_XMMREG)
869 mismatch = 1;
870 break;
871 case OPT_MemrAX: {
872 const uintptr_t *regp;
873 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY ||
874 !(regp = yasm_expr_get_reg(&op->data.ea->disp.abs, 0)) ||
875 (*regp != (X86_REG16 | 0) &&
876 *regp != (X86_REG32 | 0) &&
877 *regp != (X86_REG64 | 0)))
878 mismatch = 1;
879 break;
880 }
881 case OPT_MemEAX: {
882 const uintptr_t *regp;
883 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY ||
884 !(regp = yasm_expr_get_reg(&op->data.ea->disp.abs, 0)) ||
885 *regp != (X86_REG32 | 0))
886 mismatch = 1;
887 break;
888 }
889 case OPT_MemXMMIndex:
890 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY ||
891 !x86_expr_contains_simd(op->data.ea->disp.abs, 0))
892 mismatch = 1;
893 break;
894 case OPT_MemYMMIndex:
895 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY ||
896 !x86_expr_contains_simd(op->data.ea->disp.abs, 1))
897 mismatch = 1;
898 break;
899 default:
900 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand type"));
901 }
902
903 if (mismatch)
904 break;
905
906 /* Check operand size */
907 size = size_lookup[info_ops[i].size];
908 if (id_insn->parser == X86_PARSER_GAS) {
909 /* Require relaxed operands for GAS mode (don't allow
910 * per-operand sizing).
911 */
912 if (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG && op->size == 0) {
913 /* Register size must exactly match */
914 if (yasm_x86__get_reg_size(op->data.reg) != size)
915 mismatch = 1;
916 } else if ((info_ops[i].type == OPT_Imm
917 || info_ops[i].type == OPT_ImmNotSegOff
918 || info_ops[i].type == OPT_Imm1)
919 && !info_ops[i].relaxed
920 && info_ops[i].action != OPA_JmpRel)
921 mismatch = 1;
922 } else {
923 if (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG && op->size == 0) {
924 /* Register size must exactly match */
925 if ((bypass == 4 && i == 0) || (bypass == 5 && i == 1)
926 || (bypass == 6 && i == 2))
927 ;
928 else if (yasm_x86__get_reg_size(op->data.reg) != size)
929 mismatch = 1;
930 } else {
931 if ((bypass == 1 && i == 0) || (bypass == 2 && i == 1)
932 || (bypass == 3 && i == 2))
933 ;
934 else if (info_ops[i].relaxed) {
935 /* Relaxed checking */
936 if (size != 0 && op->size != size && op->size != 0)
937 mismatch = 1;
938 } else {
939 /* Strict checking */
940 if (op->size != size)
941 mismatch = 1;
942 }
943 }
944 }
945
946 if (mismatch)
947 break;
948
949 /* Check for 64-bit effective address size in NASM mode */
950 if (id_insn->parser != X86_PARSER_GAS &&
951 op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY) {
952 if (info_ops[i].eas64) {
953 if (op->data.ea->disp.size != 64)
954 mismatch = 1;
955 } else if (op->data.ea->disp.size == 64)
956 mismatch = 1;
957 }
958
959 if (mismatch)
960 break;
961
962 /* Check target modifier */
963 switch (info_ops[i].targetmod) {
964 case OPTM_None:
965 if (op->targetmod != 0)
966 mismatch = 1;
967 break;
968 case OPTM_Near:
969 if (op->targetmod != X86_NEAR)
970 mismatch = 1;
971 break;
972 case OPTM_Short:
973 if (op->targetmod != X86_SHORT)
974 mismatch = 1;
975 break;
976 case OPTM_Far:
977 if (op->targetmod != X86_FAR)
978 mismatch = 1;
979 break;
980 case OPTM_To:
981 if (op->targetmod != X86_TO)
982 mismatch = 1;
983 break;
984 default:
985 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid target modifier type"));
986 }
987 }
988
989 if (!mismatch) {
990 found = 1;
991 break;
992 }
993 }
994
995 if (!found)
996 return NULL;
997 return info;
998}
999
1000static void
1001x86_match_error(x86_id_insn *id_insn, yasm_insn_operand **ops,
1002 yasm_insn_operand **rev_ops, const unsigned int *size_lookup)
1003{
1004 const x86_insn_info *i;
1005 int ni;
1006 int found;
1007 int bypass;
1008
1009 /* Check for matching # of operands */
1010 found = 0;
1011 for (ni=id_insn->num_info, i=id_insn->group; ni>0; ni--, i++) {
1012 if (id_insn->insn.num_operands == i->num_operands) {
1013 found = 1;
1014 break;
1015 }
1016 }
1017 if (!found) {
1018 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TYPE, N_("invalid number of operands"));
1019 return;
1020 }
1021
1022 for (bypass=1; bypass<9; bypass++) {
1023 i = x86_find_match(id_insn, ops, rev_ops, size_lookup, bypass);
1024 if (i)
1025 break;
1026 }
1027
1028 switch (bypass) {
1029 case 1:
1030 case 4:
1031 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TYPE,
1032 N_("invalid size for operand %d"), 1);
1033 break;
1034 case 2:
1035 case 5:
1036 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TYPE,
1037 N_("invalid size for operand %d"), 2);
1038 break;
1039 case 3:
1040 case 6:
1041 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TYPE,
1042 N_("invalid size for operand %d"), 3);
1043 break;
1044 case 7:
1045 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TYPE,
1046 N_("one of source operand 1 or 3 must match dest operand"));
1047 break;
1048 case 8:
1049 {
1050 unsigned int cpu0 = i->cpu0, cpu1 = i->cpu1, cpu2 = i->cpu2;
1051 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TYPE,
1052 N_("requires CPU%s"),
1053 cpu_find_reverse(cpu0, cpu1, cpu2));
1054 break;
1055 }
1056 default:
1057 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TYPE,
1058 N_("invalid combination of opcode and operands"));
1059 }
1060}
1061
1062static void
1063x86_id_insn_finalize(yasm_bytecode *bc, yasm_bytecode *prev_bc)
1064{
1065 x86_id_insn *id_insn = (x86_id_insn *)bc->contents;
1066 x86_insn *insn;
1067 const x86_insn_info *info = id_insn->group;
1068 unsigned int mode_bits = id_insn->mode_bits;
1069 unsigned char *mod_data = id_insn->mod_data;
1070 yasm_insn_operand *op, *ops[5], *rev_ops[5];
1071 /*@null@*/ yasm_expr *imm;
1072 unsigned char im_len;
1073 unsigned char im_sign;
1074 unsigned char spare;
1075 unsigned char vexdata, vexreg;
1076 unsigned int i;
1077 unsigned int size_lookup[] = {0, 8, 16, 32, 64, 80, 128, 256, 0};
1078 unsigned long do_postop = 0;
1079
1080 size_lookup[OPS_BITS] = mode_bits;
1081
1082 yasm_insn_finalize(&id_insn->insn);
1083
1084 /* Build local array of operands from list, since we know we have a max
1085 * of 5 operands.
1086 */
1087 if (id_insn->insn.num_operands > 5) {
1088 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TYPE, N_("too many operands"));
1089 return;
1090 }
1091 ops[0] = ops[1] = ops[2] = ops[3] = ops[4] = NULL;
1092 for (i = 0, op = yasm_insn_ops_first(&id_insn->insn);
1093 op && i < id_insn->insn.num_operands;
1094 op = yasm_insn_op_next(op), i++)
1095 ops[i] = op;
1096
1097 /* If we're running in GAS mode, build a reverse array of the operands
1098 * as most GAS instructions have reversed operands from Intel style.
1099 */
1100 if (id_insn->parser == X86_PARSER_GAS) {
1101 rev_ops[0] = rev_ops[1] = rev_ops[2] = rev_ops[3] = rev_ops[4] = NULL;
1102 for (i = id_insn->insn.num_operands-1,
1103 op = yasm_insn_ops_first(&id_insn->insn);
1104 op; op = yasm_insn_op_next(op), i--)
1105 rev_ops[i] = op;
1106 }
1107
1108 /* If we're running in GAS mode, look at the first insn_info to see
1109 * if this is a relative jump (OPA_JmpRel). If so, run through the
1110 * operands and adjust for dereferences / lack thereof.
1111 */
1112 if (id_insn->parser == X86_PARSER_GAS
1113 && insn_operands[info->operands_index+0].action == OPA_JmpRel) {
1114 for (i = 0, op = ops[0]; op; op = ops[++i]) {
1115 if (!op->deref && (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG
1116 || (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY
1117 && op->data.ea->strong)))
1118 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
1119 N_("indirect call without `*'"));
1120 if (!op->deref && op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY
1121 && !op->data.ea->strong) {
1122 /* Memory that is not dereferenced, and not strong, is
1123 * actually an immediate for the purposes of relative jumps.
1124 */
1125 if (op->data.ea->segreg != 0)
1126 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
1127 N_("skipping prefixes on this instruction"));
1128 imm = op->data.ea->disp.abs;
1129 op->data.ea->disp.abs = NULL;
1130 yasm_x86__ea_destroy(op->data.ea);
1131 op->type = YASM_INSN__OPERAND_IMM;
1132 op->data.val = imm;
1133 }
1134 }
1135 }
1136
1137 info = x86_find_match(id_insn, ops, rev_ops, size_lookup, 0);
1138
1139 if (!info) {
1140 /* Didn't find a match */
1141 x86_match_error(id_insn, ops, rev_ops, size_lookup);
1142 return;
1143 }
1144
1145 if (id_insn->insn.num_operands > 0) {
1146 switch (insn_operands[info->operands_index+0].action) {
1147 case OPA_JmpRel:
1148 /* Shortcut to JmpRel */
1149 x86_finalize_jmp(bc, prev_bc, info);
1150 return;
1151 case OPA_JmpFar:
1152 /* Shortcut to JmpFar */
1153 x86_finalize_jmpfar(bc, prev_bc, info);
1154 return;
1155 }
1156 }
1157
1158 /* Copy what we can from info */
1159 insn = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(x86_insn));
1160 x86_finalize_common(&insn->common, info, mode_bits);
1161 x86_finalize_opcode(&insn->opcode, info);
1162 insn->x86_ea = NULL;
1163 imm = NULL;
1164 insn->def_opersize_64 = info->def_opersize_64;
1165 insn->special_prefix = info->special_prefix;
1166 spare = info->spare;
1167 vexdata = 0;
1168 vexreg = 0;
1169 im_len = 0;
1170 im_sign = 0;
1171 insn->postop = X86_POSTOP_NONE;
1172 insn->rex = 0;
1173
1174 /* Move VEX/XOP data (stored in special prefix) to separate location to
1175 * allow overriding of special prefix by modifiers.
1176 */
1177 if ((insn->special_prefix & 0xF0) == 0xC0 ||
1178 (insn->special_prefix & 0xF0) == 0x80) {
1179 vexdata = insn->special_prefix;
1180 insn->special_prefix = 0;
1181 }
1182
1183 /* Apply modifiers */
1184 for (i=0; i<NELEMS(info->modifiers); i++) {
1185 switch (info->modifiers[i]) {
1186 case MOD_Gap:
1187 break;
1188 case MOD_PreAdd:
1189 insn->special_prefix += mod_data[i];
1190 break;
1191 case MOD_Op0Add:
1192 insn->opcode.opcode[0] += mod_data[i];
1193 break;
1194 case MOD_Op1Add:
1195 insn->opcode.opcode[1] += mod_data[i];
1196 break;
1197 case MOD_Op2Add:
1198 insn->opcode.opcode[2] += mod_data[i];
1199 break;
1200 case MOD_SpAdd:
1201 spare += mod_data[i];
1202 break;
1203 case MOD_OpSizeR:
1204 insn->common.opersize = mod_data[i];
1205 break;
1206 case MOD_Imm8:
1207 imm = yasm_expr_create_ident(yasm_expr_int(
1208 yasm_intnum_create_uint(mod_data[i])), bc->line);
1209 im_len = 8;
1210 break;
1211 case MOD_DOpS64R:
1212 insn->def_opersize_64 = mod_data[i];
1213 break;
1214 case MOD_Op1AddSp:
1215 insn->opcode.opcode[1] += mod_data[i]<<3;
1216 break;
1217 case MOD_SetVEX:
1218 vexdata = mod_data[i];
1219 break;
1220 default:
1221 break;
1222 }
1223 }
1224
1225 /* In 64-bit mode, if opersize is 64 and default is not 64,
1226 * force REX byte.
1227 */
1228 if (mode_bits == 64 && insn->common.opersize == 64 &&
1229 insn->def_opersize_64 != 64)
1230 insn->rex = 0x48;
1231
1232 /* Go through operands and assign */
1233 if (id_insn->insn.num_operands > 0) {
1234 yasm_insn_operand **use_ops = ops;
1235 const x86_info_operand *info_ops =
1236 &insn_operands[info->operands_index];
1237
1238 /* Use reversed operands in GAS mode if not otherwise specified */
1239 if (id_insn->parser == X86_PARSER_GAS
1240 && !(info->gas_flags & GAS_NO_REV))
1241 use_ops = rev_ops;
1242
1243 for (i = 0, op = use_ops[0]; op && i<info->num_operands;
1244 op = use_ops[++i]) {
1245 switch (info_ops[i].action) {
1246 case OPA_None:
1247 /* Throw away the operand contents */
1248 switch (op->type) {
1249 case YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG:
1250 case YASM_INSN__OPERAND_SEGREG:
1251 break;
1252 case YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY:
1253 yasm_x86__ea_destroy(op->data.ea);
1254 break;
1255 case YASM_INSN__OPERAND_IMM:
1256 yasm_expr_destroy(op->data.val);
1257 break;
1258 }
1259 break;
1260 case OPA_EA:
1261 switch (op->type) {
1262 case YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG:
1263 insn->x86_ea =
1264 yasm_x86__ea_create_reg(insn->x86_ea,
1265 (unsigned long)op->data.reg, &insn->rex,
1266 mode_bits);
1267 break;
1268 case YASM_INSN__OPERAND_SEGREG:
1269 yasm_internal_error(
1270 N_("invalid operand conversion"));
1271 case YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY:
1272 if (op->seg)
1273 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE,
1274 N_("invalid segment in effective address"));
1275 insn->x86_ea = (x86_effaddr *)op->data.ea;
1276 if (info_ops[i].type == OPT_MemOffs)
1277 /* Special-case for MOV MemOffs instruction */
1278 yasm_x86__ea_set_disponly(insn->x86_ea);
1279 else if (info_ops[i].type == OPT_MemXMMIndex) {
1280 /* Remember VSIB mode */
1281 insn->x86_ea->vsib_mode = 1;
1282 insn->x86_ea->need_sib = 1;
1283 } else if (info_ops[i].type == OPT_MemYMMIndex) {
1284 /* Remember VSIB mode */
1285 insn->x86_ea->vsib_mode = 2;
1286 insn->x86_ea->need_sib = 1;
1287 } else if (id_insn->default_rel &&
1288 !op->data.ea->not_pc_rel &&
1289 op->data.ea->segreg != 0x6404 &&
1290 op->data.ea->segreg != 0x6505 &&
1291 !yasm_expr__contains(
1292 op->data.ea->disp.abs, YASM_EXPR_REG))
1293 /* Enable default PC-rel if no regs and segreg
1294 * is not FS or GS.
1295 */
1296 insn->x86_ea->ea.pc_rel = 1;
1297 break;
1298 case YASM_INSN__OPERAND_IMM:
1299 insn->x86_ea =
1300 yasm_x86__ea_create_imm(insn->x86_ea,
1301 op->data.val,
1302 size_lookup[info_ops[i].size]);
1303 break;
1304 }
1305 break;
1306 case OPA_EAVEX:
1307 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG)
1308 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand conversion"));
1309 insn->x86_ea =
1310 yasm_x86__ea_create_reg(insn->x86_ea,
1311 (unsigned long)op->data.reg, &insn->rex, mode_bits);
1312 vexreg = op->data.reg & 0xF;
1313 break;
1314 case OPA_Imm:
1315 if (op->seg)
1316 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE,
1317 N_("immediate does not support segment"));
1318 if (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_IMM) {
1319 imm = op->data.val;
1320 im_len = size_lookup[info_ops[i].size];
1321 } else
1322 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand conversion"));
1323 break;
1324 case OPA_SImm:
1325 if (op->seg)
1326 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_VALUE,
1327 N_("immediate does not support segment"));
1328 if (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_IMM) {
1329 imm = op->data.val;
1330 im_len = size_lookup[info_ops[i].size];
1331 im_sign = 1;
1332 } else
1333 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand conversion"));
1334 break;
1335 case OPA_Spare:
1336 if (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_SEGREG)
1337 spare = (unsigned char)(op->data.reg&7);
1338 else if (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG) {
1339 if (yasm_x86__set_rex_from_reg(&insn->rex, &spare,
1340 op->data.reg, mode_bits, X86_REX_R))
1341 return;
1342 } else
1343 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand conversion"));
1344 break;
1345 case OPA_SpareVEX:
1346 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG)
1347 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand conversion"));
1348 if (yasm_x86__set_rex_from_reg(&insn->rex, &spare,
1349 op->data.reg, mode_bits, X86_REX_R))
1350 return;
1351 vexreg = op->data.reg & 0xF;
1352 break;
1353 case OPA_Op0Add:
1354 if (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG) {
1355 unsigned char opadd;
1356 if (yasm_x86__set_rex_from_reg(&insn->rex, &opadd,
1357 op->data.reg, mode_bits, X86_REX_B))
1358 return;
1359 insn->opcode.opcode[0] += opadd;
1360 } else
1361 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand conversion"));
1362 break;
1363 case OPA_Op1Add:
1364 if (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG) {
1365 unsigned char opadd;
1366 if (yasm_x86__set_rex_from_reg(&insn->rex, &opadd,
1367 op->data.reg, mode_bits, X86_REX_B))
1368 return;
1369 insn->opcode.opcode[1] += opadd;
1370 } else
1371 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand conversion"));
1372 break;
1373 case OPA_SpareEA:
1374 if (op->type == YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG) {
1375 insn->x86_ea =
1376 yasm_x86__ea_create_reg(insn->x86_ea,
1377 (unsigned long)op->data.reg, &insn->rex,
1378 mode_bits);
1379 if (!insn->x86_ea ||
1380 yasm_x86__set_rex_from_reg(&insn->rex, &spare,
1381 op->data.reg, mode_bits, X86_REX_R)) {
1382 if (insn->x86_ea)
1383 yasm_xfree(insn->x86_ea);
1384 yasm_xfree(insn);
1385 return;
1386 }
1387 } else
1388 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand conversion"));
1389 break;
1390 case OPA_AdSizeEA: {
1391 const uintptr_t *regp = NULL;
1392 /* Only implement this for OPT_MemrAX and OPT_MemEAX
1393 * for now.
1394 */
1395 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_MEMORY ||
1396 !(regp = yasm_expr_get_reg(&op->data.ea->disp.abs, 0)))
1397 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand conversion"));
1398 /* 64-bit mode does not allow 16-bit addresses */
1399 if (mode_bits == 64 && *regp == (X86_REG16 | 0))
1400 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TYPE,
1401 N_("16-bit addresses not supported in 64-bit mode"));
1402 else if (*regp == (X86_REG16 | 0))
1403 insn->common.addrsize = 16;
1404 else if (*regp == (X86_REG32 | 0))
1405 insn->common.addrsize = 32;
1406 else if (mode_bits == 64 && *regp == (X86_REG64 | 0))
1407 insn->common.addrsize = 64;
1408 else
1409 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TYPE,
1410 N_("unsupported address size"));
1411 yasm_x86__ea_destroy(op->data.ea);
1412 break;
1413 }
1414 case OPA_VEX:
1415 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG)
1416 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand conversion"));
1417 vexreg = op->data.reg & 0xF;
1418 break;
1419 case OPA_VEXImmSrc:
1420 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_REG)
1421 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand conversion"));
1422
1423 if (!imm) {
1424 imm = yasm_expr_create_ident(
1425 yasm_expr_int(
1426 yasm_intnum_create_uint((op->data.reg << 4)
1427 & 0xF0)),
1428 bc->line);
1429 } else {
1430 imm = yasm_expr_create(
1431 YASM_EXPR_OR,
1432 yasm_expr_expr(yasm_expr_create(
1433 YASM_EXPR_AND,
1434 yasm_expr_expr(imm),
1435 yasm_expr_int(yasm_intnum_create_uint(0x0F)),
1436 bc->line)),
1437 yasm_expr_int(
1438 yasm_intnum_create_uint((op->data.reg << 4)
1439 & 0xF0)),
1440 bc->line);
1441 }
1442 im_len = 8;
1443 break;
1444 case OPA_VEXImm:
1445 if (op->type != YASM_INSN__OPERAND_IMM)
1446 yasm_internal_error(N_("invalid operand conversion"));
1447
1448 if (!imm)
1449 imm = op->data.val;
1450 else {
1451 imm = yasm_expr_create(
1452 YASM_EXPR_OR,
1453 yasm_expr_expr(yasm_expr_create(
1454 YASM_EXPR_AND,
1455 yasm_expr_expr(op->data.val),
1456 yasm_expr_int(yasm_intnum_create_uint(0x0F)),
1457 bc->line)),
1458 yasm_expr_expr(yasm_expr_create(
1459 YASM_EXPR_AND,
1460 yasm_expr_expr(imm),
1461 yasm_expr_int(yasm_intnum_create_uint(0xF0)),
1462 bc->line)),
1463 bc->line);
1464 }
1465 im_len = 8;
1466 break;
1467 default:
1468 yasm_internal_error(N_("unknown operand action"));
1469 }
1470
1471 if (info_ops[i].size == OPS_BITS)
1472 insn->common.opersize = (unsigned char)mode_bits;
1473
1474 switch (info_ops[i].post_action) {
1475 case OPAP_None:
1476 break;
1477 case OPAP_SImm8:
1478 /* Check operand strictness; if strict and non-8-bit,
1479 * pre-emptively expand to full size.
1480 * For unspecified size case, still optimize.
1481 */
1482 if (!(id_insn->force_strict || op->strict)
1483 || op->size == 0)
1484 insn->postop = X86_POSTOP_SIGNEXT_IMM8;
1485 else if (op->size != 8) {
1486 insn->opcode.opcode[0] =
1487 insn->opcode.opcode[insn->opcode.len];
1488 insn->opcode.len = 1;
1489 }
1490 break;
1491 case OPAP_ShortMov:
1492 do_postop = OPAP_ShortMov;
1493 break;
1494 case OPAP_A16:
1495 insn->postop = X86_POSTOP_ADDRESS16;
1496 break;
1497 case OPAP_SImm32Avail:
1498 do_postop = OPAP_SImm32Avail;
1499 break;
1500 default:
1501 yasm_internal_error(
1502 N_("unknown operand postponed action"));
1503 }
1504 }
1505 }
1506
1507 if (insn->x86_ea) {
1508 yasm_x86__ea_init(insn->x86_ea, spare, prev_bc);
1509 for (i=0; i<id_insn->insn.num_segregs; i++)
1510 yasm_ea_set_segreg(&insn->x86_ea->ea, id_insn->insn.segregs[i]);
1511 } else if (id_insn->insn.num_segregs > 0 && insn->special_prefix == 0) {
1512 if (id_insn->insn.num_segregs > 1)
1513 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
1514 N_("multiple segment overrides, using leftmost"));
1515 insn->special_prefix = (unsigned char)
1516 (id_insn->insn.segregs[id_insn->insn.num_segregs-1]>>8);
1517 } else if (id_insn->insn.num_segregs > 0)
1518 yasm_internal_error(N_("unhandled segment prefix"));
1519
1520 if (imm) {
1521 insn->imm = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(yasm_value));
1522 if (yasm_value_finalize_expr(insn->imm, imm, prev_bc, im_len))
1523 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_TOO_COMPLEX,
1524 N_("immediate expression too complex"));
1525 insn->imm->sign = im_sign;
1526 } else
1527 insn->imm = NULL;
1528
1529 yasm_x86__bc_apply_prefixes((x86_common *)insn, &insn->rex,
1530 insn->def_opersize_64,
1531 id_insn->insn.num_prefixes,
1532 id_insn->insn.prefixes);
1533
1534 if (insn->postop == X86_POSTOP_ADDRESS16 && insn->common.addrsize) {
1535 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL, N_("address size override ignored"));
1536 insn->common.addrsize = 0;
1537 }
1538
1539 /* Handle non-span-dependent post-ops here */
1540 switch (do_postop) {
1541 case OPAP_ShortMov:
1542 /* Long (modrm+sib) mov instructions in amd64 can be optimized into
1543 * short mov instructions if a 32-bit address override is applied in
1544 * 64-bit mode to an EA of just an offset (no registers) and the
1545 * target register is al/ax/eax/rax.
1546 *
1547 * We don't want to do this if we're in default rel mode.
1548 */
1549 if (!id_insn->default_rel &&
1550 insn->common.mode_bits == 64 &&
1551 insn->common.addrsize == 32 &&
1552 (!insn->x86_ea->ea.disp.abs ||
1553 !yasm_expr__contains(insn->x86_ea->ea.disp.abs,
1554 YASM_EXPR_REG))) {
1555 yasm_x86__ea_set_disponly(insn->x86_ea);
1556 /* Make the short form permanent. */
1557 insn->opcode.opcode[0] = insn->opcode.opcode[1];
1558 }
1559 insn->opcode.opcode[1] = 0; /* avoid possible confusion */
1560 break;
1561 case OPAP_SImm32Avail:
1562 /* Used for 64-bit mov immediate, which can take a sign-extended
1563 * imm32 as well as imm64 values. The imm32 form is put in the
1564 * second byte of the opcode and its ModRM byte is put in the third
1565 * byte of the opcode.
1566 */
1567 if (!insn->imm->abs ||
1568 (yasm_expr_get_intnum(&insn->imm->abs, 0) &&
1569 yasm_intnum_check_size(
1570 yasm_expr_get_intnum(&insn->imm->abs, 0), 32, 0, 1))) {
1571 /* Throwaway REX byte */
1572 unsigned char rex_temp = 0;
1573
1574 /* Build ModRM EA - CAUTION: this depends on
1575 * opcode 0 being a mov instruction!
1576 */
1577 insn->x86_ea = yasm_x86__ea_create_reg(insn->x86_ea,
1578 (unsigned long)insn->opcode.opcode[0]-0xB8, &rex_temp, 64);
1579
1580 /* Make the imm32s form permanent. */
1581 insn->opcode.opcode[0] = insn->opcode.opcode[1];
1582 insn->imm->size = 32;
1583 }
1584 insn->opcode.opcode[1] = 0; /* avoid possible confusion */
1585 break;
1586 default:
1587 break;
1588 }
1589
1590 /* Convert to VEX/XOP prefixes if requested.
1591 * To save space in the insn structure, the VEX/XOP prefix is written into
1592 * special_prefix and the first 2 bytes of the instruction are set to
1593 * the second two VEX/XOP bytes. During calc_len() it may be shortened to
1594 * one VEX byte (this can only be done after knowledge of REX value); this
1595 * further optimization is not possible for XOP.
1596 */
1597 if (vexdata) {
1598 int xop = ((vexdata & 0xF0) == 0x80);
1599 unsigned char vex1 = 0xE0; /* R=X=B=1, mmmmm=0 */
1600 unsigned char vex2;
1601
1602 if (xop) {
1603 /* Look at the first bytes of the opcode for the XOP mmmmm field.
1604 * Leave R=X=B=1 for now.
1605 */
1606 if (insn->opcode.opcode[0] != 0x08 &&
1607 insn->opcode.opcode[0] != 0x09 &&
1608 insn->opcode.opcode[0] != 0x0A)
1609 yasm_internal_error(N_("first opcode byte of XOP must be 0x08, 0x09, or 0x0A"));
1610 vex1 |= insn->opcode.opcode[0];
1611 /* Move opcode byte back one byte to make room for XOP prefix. */
1612 insn->opcode.opcode[2] = insn->opcode.opcode[1];
1613 } else {
1614 /* Look at the first bytes of the opcode to see what leading bytes
1615 * to encode in the VEX mmmmm field. Leave R=X=B=1 for now.
1616 */
1617 if (insn->opcode.opcode[0] != 0x0F)
1618 yasm_internal_error(N_("first opcode byte of VEX must be 0x0F"));
1619
1620 if (insn->opcode.opcode[1] == 0x38)
1621 vex1 |= 0x02; /* implied 0x0F 0x38 */
1622 else if (insn->opcode.opcode[1] == 0x3A)
1623 vex1 |= 0x03; /* implied 0x0F 0x3A */
1624 else {
1625 /* Originally a 0F-only opcode; move opcode byte back one
1626 * position to make room for VEX prefix.
1627 */
1628 insn->opcode.opcode[2] = insn->opcode.opcode[1];
1629 vex1 |= 0x01; /* implied 0x0F */
1630 }
1631 }
1632
1633 /* Check for update of special prefix by modifiers */
1634 if (insn->special_prefix != 0) {
1635 vexdata &= ~0x03;
1636 switch (insn->special_prefix) {
1637 case 0x66:
1638 vexdata |= 0x01;
1639 break;
1640 case 0xF3:
1641 vexdata |= 0x02;
1642 break;
1643 case 0xF2:
1644 vexdata |= 0x03;
1645 break;
1646 default:
1647 yasm_internal_error(N_("unrecognized special prefix"));
1648 }
1649 }
1650
1651 /* 2nd VEX byte is WvvvvLpp.
1652 * W, L, pp come from vexdata
1653 * vvvv comes from 1s complement of vexreg
1654 */
1655 vex2 = (((vexdata & 0x8) << 4) | /* W */
1656 ((15 - (vexreg & 0xF)) << 3) | /* vvvv */
1657 (vexdata & 0x7)); /* Lpp */
1658
1659 /* Save to special_prefix and opcode */
1660 insn->special_prefix = xop ? 0x8F : 0xC4; /* VEX/XOP prefix */
1661 insn->opcode.opcode[0] = vex1;
1662 insn->opcode.opcode[1] = vex2;
1663 insn->opcode.len = 3; /* two prefix bytes and 1 opcode byte */
1664 }
1665
1666 x86_id_insn_clear_operands(id_insn);
1667
1668 /* Transform the bytecode */
1669 yasm_x86__bc_transform_insn(bc, insn);
1670}

1675
1676 /* instruction parse group - NULL if prefix */
1677 /*@null@*/ const x86_insn_info *group;
1678

1680 * For prefix, prefix type shifted right by 8.
1681 */
1682 unsigned int num_info:8;

1790
1791yasm_arch_insnprefix
1792yasm_x86__parse_check_insnprefix(yasm_arch *arch, const char *id,
1793 size_t id_len, unsigned long line,
1794 yasm_bytecode **bc, uintptr_t *prefix)
1795{
1796 yasm_arch_x86 *arch_x86 = (yasm_arch_x86 *)arch;
1797 /*@null@*/ const insnprefix_parse_data *pdata;
1798 size_t i;
1799 static char lcaseid[17];
1800
1801 *bc = (yasm_bytecode *)NULL;
1802 *prefix = 0;
1803
1804 if (id_len > 16)
1805 return YASM_ARCH_NOTINSNPREFIX;
1806 for (i=0; i<id_len; i++)
1807 lcaseid[i] = tolower(id[i]);
1808 lcaseid[id_len] = '\0';
1809
1810 switch (PARSER(arch_x86)) {
1811 case X86_PARSER_NASM:
1812 pdata = insnprefix_nasm_find(lcaseid, id_len);
1813 break;
1814 case X86_PARSER_TASM:
1815 pdata = insnprefix_nasm_find(lcaseid, id_len);
1816 break;
1817 case X86_PARSER_GAS:
1818 pdata = insnprefix_gas_find(lcaseid, id_len);
1819 break;
1820 default:
1821 pdata = NULL;
1822 }
1823 if (!pdata)
1824 return YASM_ARCH_NOTINSNPREFIX;
1825
1826 if (pdata->group) {
1827 x86_id_insn *id_insn;
1828 wordptr cpu_enabled = arch_x86->cpu_enables[arch_x86->active_cpu];
1829 unsigned int cpu0, cpu1, cpu2;
1830
1831 if (arch_x86->mode_bits != 64 && (pdata->misc_flags & ONLY_64)) {
1832 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
1833 N_("`%s' is an instruction in 64-bit mode"), id);
1834 return YASM_ARCH_NOTINSNPREFIX;
1835 }
1836 if (arch_x86->mode_bits == 64 && (pdata->misc_flags & NOT_64)) {
1837 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_GENERAL,
1838 N_("`%s' invalid in 64-bit mode"), id);
1839 id_insn = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(x86_id_insn));
1840 yasm_insn_initialize(&id_insn->insn);
1841 id_insn->group = not64_insn;
1842 id_insn->cpu_enabled = cpu_enabled;
1843 id_insn->mod_data[0] = 0;
1844 id_insn->mod_data[1] = 0;
1845 id_insn->mod_data[2] = 0;
1846 id_insn->num_info = NELEMS(not64_insn);
1847 id_insn->mode_bits = arch_x86->mode_bits;
1848 id_insn->suffix = 0;
1849 id_insn->misc_flags = 0;
1850 id_insn->parser = PARSER(arch_x86);
1851
1852 id_insn->force_strict = arch_x86->force_strict != 0;
1853 id_insn->default_rel = arch_x86->default_rel != 0;
1854 *bc = yasm_bc_create_common(&x86_id_insn_callback, id_insn, line);
1855 return YASM_ARCH_INSN;
1856 }
1857
1858 cpu0 = pdata->cpu0;
1859 cpu1 = pdata->cpu1;
1860 cpu2 = pdata->cpu2;
1861
1862 if (!BitVector_bit_test(cpu_enabled, cpu0) ||
1863 !BitVector_bit_test(cpu_enabled, cpu1) ||
1864 !BitVector_bit_test(cpu_enabled, cpu2)) {
1865 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
1866 N_("`%s' is an instruction in CPU%s"), id,
1867 cpu_find_reverse(cpu0, cpu1, cpu2));
1868 return YASM_ARCH_NOTINSNPREFIX;
1869 }
1870
1871 id_insn = yasm_xmalloc(sizeof(x86_id_insn));
1872 yasm_insn_initialize(&id_insn->insn);
1873 id_insn->group = pdata->group;
1874 id_insn->cpu_enabled = cpu_enabled;
1875 id_insn->mod_data[0] = pdata->mod_data0;
1876 id_insn->mod_data[1] = pdata->mod_data1;
1877 id_insn->mod_data[2] = pdata->mod_data2;
1878 id_insn->num_info = pdata->num_info;
1879 id_insn->mode_bits = arch_x86->mode_bits;
1880 id_insn->suffix = pdata->flags;
1881 id_insn->misc_flags = pdata->misc_flags;
1882 id_insn->parser = PARSER(arch_x86);
1883 id_insn->force_strict = arch_x86->force_strict != 0;
1884 id_insn->default_rel = arch_x86->default_rel != 0;
1885 *bc = yasm_bc_create_common(&x86_id_insn_callback, id_insn, line);
1886 return YASM_ARCH_INSN;
1887 } else {
1888 unsigned long type = pdata->num_info<<8;
1889 unsigned long value = pdata->flags;
1890
1891 if (arch_x86->mode_bits == 64 && type == X86_OPERSIZE && value == 32) {
1892 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_GENERAL,
1893 N_("Cannot override data size to 32 bits in 64-bit mode"));
1894 return YASM_ARCH_NOTINSNPREFIX;
1895 }
1896
1897 if (arch_x86->mode_bits == 64 && type == X86_ADDRSIZE && value == 16) {
1898 yasm_error_set(YASM_ERROR_GENERAL,
1899 N_("Cannot override address size to 16 bits in 64-bit mode"));
1900 return YASM_ARCH_NOTINSNPREFIX;
1901 }
1902
1903 if (arch_x86->mode_bits != 64 && (pdata->misc_flags & ONLY_64)) {
1904 yasm_warn_set(YASM_WARN_GENERAL,
1905 N_("`%s' is a prefix in 64-bit mode"), id);
1906 return YASM_ARCH_NOTINSNPREFIX;
1907 }
1908 *prefix = type|value;
1909 return YASM_ARCH_PREFIX;
1910 }
1911}
